As all of you know, Japan has been struck by a string of natural disasters
the past month, starting with the massive earthquake, to the tsunami, and
now a nuclear crisis. As members of the IMSA community, it is part of our
role as leaders to continue to be informed and respond to this disaster.
More information can be found in the following links:

http://topics.nytimes.com/top/news/international/countriesandterritories/japan/index.html
http://news.yahoo.com/s/yblog_thelookout/20110316/ts_yblog_thelookout/japans-nuclear-crisis-where-things-stand
http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-12307698

This Thursday, April 14th from 4:30-5:30 in the AC Pit, Dr. Smith and Dr.
Dong will be giving a short presentation about the current situation and
answer any questions. Dr. Dong will be presenting about science behind the
crisis (nuclear energy) and Dr. Smith will be talking about the political
and social policies involved.

Recap:
What: Dr. Smith and Dr. Dong will be giving a presentation as well as
answer any questions related to the situation in Japan
When: 4:30-5:30
Where: AC Pit
Why: Because this is a great opportunity to learn about world issues and
how we can respond to the need.

Refreshments will be provided after the event where students will be able
to share ideas and discuss more about Japan.